summary: FDA OKs Powerful New Opioid Despite Criticisms
title: FDA OKs Powerful New Opioid Despite Criticisms
body:
An FDA advisory committee did recommend for approval of Dsuvia in a 10-3 vote last month.  But the committee’s chair took the highly unusual move of voicing his opposition at that time. Dr. Raeford Brown, a professor of anesthesiology and pediatrics at the University of Kentucky, urged the FDA to reject the drug.



source https://www.webmd.com/pain-management/news/20181102/fda-oks-powerful-new-opioid-despite-criticisms?src=RSS_PUBLIC

summary:
🔴 Vuoi mantenere attivo il tuo sistema immunitario prima dell'arrivo dell’#inverno?
Escursioni termiche, stress, inquinamento,...
body:
🔴 Vuoi mantenere attivo il tuo sistema immunitario prima dell'arrivo dell’#inverno?

Escursioni termiche, stress, inquinamento, uno stile di vita scorretto e un’alimentazione non adeguata, possono renderci vulnerabili nella stagione invernale.

Daigo® Immuno, integratore alimentare di Magnesio, Potassio, Zinco, Vitamine B6, B12 e C, con estratti di Echinacea, Rodiola e Propoli, può essere un aiuto per ricaricare l’organismo in questo momento dell’anno.

Magnesio e Vitamina C contrastano la stanchezza e l’affaticamento. Zinco e Vitamina C contribuiscono al buon funzionamento del sistema immunitario ed alla protezione delle cellule dallo stress ossidativo. L’#Echinacea insieme alle Vitamine B6 e B12 supportano le naturali difese dell’organismo. La Rodiola per la sua azione tonico-adattogena è utile contro la stanchezza sia fisica che mentale.

💊Modalità d'uso

Si consiglia l’assunzione di una bustina al giorno e comunque non più di due bustine nell’arco della giornata. Sciogliere il contenuto di una bustina (4 g) in circa un bicchiere di acqua (80-100 mL). A piacimento, è possibile sciogliere il contenuto della bustina in una tazza di acqua calda (Non bollente).

summary:
Been feeling like crap training so it was time to do some assessment.
As with so many it wasn't what I was doing in the gym that...
caption:
Been feeling like crap training so it was time to do some assessment.
As with so many it wasn’t what I was doing in the gym that needed to be fixed.

Put Omega-3s back into my supplementation.
Try to solve the not sleeping properly issue.
Drink more water.
Get more protein.

Also gotta stress the importance of surrounding yourself with the right people. Doesn’t matter how many certs you have or what you’ve learned. When you’re in a rut you need others to remind you of the things you should already know to make shit happen.
Thanks @charliftsalot & @robertwagner10

#training #fitness #supplements #sleep #health #steelsharpenssteel #gettingbackontrack #whydoisuck #makechange #flinndalsport

summary: Dropped 20kg. Inspired my dad to work out with me, he wants to drop 30-40kg but only wants to do weights. Advice? via /r/Fitness
title: Dropped 20kg. Inspired my dad to work out with me, he wants to drop 30-40kg but only wants to do weights. Advice? via /r/Fitness
body:
First off I understand the importance of nutrition, especially for weight loss, I’m working on that with him first don’t worry about that.

Ss exercise is concerned, I’m looking for a routine that will help burn calories effectively but in a way that can be presented as a weightlifting routine. I’ve tried to convince him to do bodyweight exercises but he won’t have it, the “excessive sweating and jiggling” puts him off. Would just doing a program like 5/3/1 help him burn much fat? I’m just not too sure what my options are here.

Thanks

summary: Is anything wrong with my routine? via /r/Fitness
title: Is anything wrong with my routine? via /r/Fitness
body:
Been following GSLP for almost 3 months (will be 3 months in 2 weeks) I’m on a deficit and I can see results but as of late it’s getting harder to add weight every session. Sometimes for lack of plates I add more than the recommended adding weight, I’m guessing I’m going too fast hence the difficulty to add more weight so to counter this, I train 5 days instead of the program 3 days. On the 2 extra days , I work on isolation and keep hitting the 3 day recommended exercises. At what point do I switch from GSLP to a split?I still have to lose 4lbs to be at 12%BF and lean bulk so I’m guessing stalling is just around the corner. Also, if you could look at my added exercises and see if they are coherent and sufficient would be grateful.

Day 1 of GSLP = BP+ BR+ S then I add: Leg extensions, leg curls and back extension Rest day of the program I do : lunges, calf raises, mountain climber, leg extension + leg curls

Day 2 of GSLP: OHP + Lat pull downs + chin ups + DL then I add arnold press+ lateral raise Rest day of the program I do: shrugs front raise + reverse fly+ bicep curl + tricep extension + chest fly

Day 3 of GSLP: BP+ BR+ S then I add crunches + hanging knee raise + reverse crunch + weighted russian twist and superman.

Thanks for reading
